<StringTableFile xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema">
  <Name>conversations\26_uncharted_islands\26_cv_cannibal_soulread</Name>
  <NextEntryID>1</NextEntryID>
  <EntryCount>9</EntryCount>
  <Entries>
    <Entry>
      <ID>1</ID>
      <DefaultText>Never have I known such hunger. It gnaws at me, robs me of thought, of will. I cannot sleep for the pain. This barren island is a curse. How unlucky we are to be stranded here, where not even grass will grow. If we don't find food soon, all of us will surely perish.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>2</ID>
      <DefaultText>I wake from fitful half-sleep to find my crew standing in a ring above me. Their faces are drawn and haggard, their hair unkempt. I try to ask them why they've woken me, if something has happened, but I cannot form the words.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>3</ID>
      <DefaultText>Arlendr kneels beside me. His words are muffled, faint - I hear them as if from the bottom of a well. He seems to be saying goodbye. But where will he go? He raises his knife, and his eyes are wet with unshed tears. A bright horror blooms in me, terror floods my veins, these are my comrades, my friends, they wouldn't -</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>4</ID>
      <DefaultText>A jumbled pile of human remains in various states of decomposition lies stacked against a wall. Some of the bones are recognizable - femurs, mandibles, ribs - while others are cracked or splintered, marrow sucked clean. You sense a soul still lingering among the debris.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>5</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Reach for the soul.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>6</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Leave.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>7</ID>
      <DefaultText>I notice then that each of them bears a weapon - some machetes, others rocks. Arlendr grips his knife. From what might they need to protect themselves in this miserable place?</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>8</ID>
      <DefaultText>Warmth spills down my chest. Darkness edges my vision. And I am suddenly tired, so tired. &lt;i&gt;I'm sorry,&lt;/i&gt; he said. &lt;i&gt;I'm sorry.&lt;/i&gt;</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>9</ID>
      <DefaultText>Xoti thrusts out her lantern, and the light inside flares as another soul is harvested.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
  </Entries>
</StringTableFile>